Defendant in custody.
On counts 1, 3 and 5, the defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of three and one-half (3.5) years.  That is eighteen (18) months initial confinement followed by twenty-four (24) months extended supervision, on each count, consecutive.
The Court finds the defendant not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program.
The defendant is given credit of 102 days on count 1.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Pay court costs;
2) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) maintain fulltime employment or work search;
4) maintain absolute sobriety;
5) AODA assessment and follow through;
6) Comply with all child support orders;
7) Follow all payment obligations ordered by the Child Support Agency.
Minutes.
